es of their lives. Please note the capacity for this event is very limited and therefore tickets will be allocated on a first come first served basis, with a maximum of 2 per organisation. Programme 08:30 Arrivals for registration and breakfast 09:00 Welcome Adara Wicaksono, Programme Manager, NLA Athina Stylianidi, Associate, Jestico + Whiles Alex Luria, Associate, Jestico + Whiles09:10 Tour begins 10:00 End Speaker biographies Athina Stylianidi Associate, Jestico + Whiles Alex Luria Associate, Jestico + Whiles Adara Wicaksono Programme Manager, NLA	Study Tour: Greenwich Millennium Village	Explore the innovative final phase of Greenwich Millennium Village, a testament to collaborative urban planning and residential design. Join this exclusive tour on 03 September 2025.	Explore the innovative final phase of Greenwich Millennium Village, a testament to collaborative urban planning and residential design.	Discover the culmination of a 25-year master plan at Greenwich Millennium Village, an exceptional development providing 1,746 new homes. This study tour offers a unique opportunity to see the final phase, designed by Jestico + Whiles in partnership with Peter Barber Architects and Studio 54 Architecture. The scheme impressively recalls Ralph Erskines playful evolutionary tradition, integrating streets and squares that foster a strong sense of community. Located on Londons Greenwich Peninsula, the site showcases a human-scale approach, prioritising street life, pedestrians, and cyclists. Learn how the collaborative design process resulted in unique plots within a cohesive urban fabric, creating diverse and engaging spaces. The focus on traditional patterns like squares, avenues, and mews facilitates organic interactions between residents and their environment, promoting a vibrant community where people desire to live through various life stages. This tour provides valuable insights into successful large-scale residential development and urban design.	03 Sep 2025, 08:3