rtable shoes for walking.Dont miss this opportunity to see an award-winning sustainable neighbourhood firsthand and learn directly from the architects behind its inspiring design.	RIBA East: Knights Park walking tour	Join an exclusive guided walking tour of Knights Park, an award-winning, net-zero carbon residential development in Cambridge, led by the architects Michael Mueller and Alexis Butterfield. This event takes place on 11 September 2025.	Join an exclusive guided walking tour of Knights Park, an award-winning, net-zero carbon residential development in Cambridge, led by the architects Michael Mueller and Alexis Butterfield.	Discover the innovative design and sustainable principles behind Knights Park, an acclaimed residential development in Eddington, Cambridge, on this exclusive guided walking tour. Led by Michael Mueller of Alison Brooks Architects and Alexis Butterfield of Pollard Thomas Edwards, the tour offers a unique opportunity to explore a low-rise, high-density community that sets a new standard for sustainable urban living.\n\nKnights Park, a key part of the University of Cambridges urban extension, features 249 homes designed to Code for Sustainable Homes Level 5. You'll gain firsthand insight into its collaborative master planning, which seamlessly integrates diverse housing types with tree-lined avenues, green streets, and distinctive palazzo-style apartment buildings. The tour will highlight how architecture, landscape, and urban design converge to create a vibrant, future-proofed neighbourhood that promotes active travel, biodiversity, and a strong sense of place. This event is incredibly useful for architects interested in learning how to deliver sustainable, adaptable, and high-quality housing at scale within a cohesive urban framework.	11 Sep 2025, 10:0012:00	20250911	Knights Park Sales & Marketing Suite, Eddington Avenue, Girton, CB3 1SE, Cambridge, UK	Free	t	16216	draft	2025-08-04 16:41:46.326687	2025-08-04 15:16:20.378988	171
993	https://www.architecture.com/whats-on/riba-bristol-and-bath-hauser-wirth-tour	riba	Title: RIBA Bristol and Bath: Hauser & Wirth Tour\\nEvent Type: Tours\\nShort Description: Explore this pioneering contemporary gallery, multipurpose arts centre and community destination created from a former farmstead in rural Somerset.\\nDate: 11 September 2025, 1pm to 4pm\\nPlace: Hauser & Wirth, Dropping Lane, Bruton, Somerset, BA10 0NL\\nCost: 6.13\\nDescription: Join RIBA Bristol and Bath for a special afternoon at Hauser & Wirth Somerset, an award-winning gallery and arts centre with award winning landscaping and feature garden by Piet Oudolf.The event includes an architect's tour of the site with the opportunity to stay and relax in the special surroundings for refreshments and networking.Expect an engaging guided experience exploring how contemporary art meets innovative rural architecture. The site itself  featuring a converted farmstead, landscaped gardens, and inspiring exhibition spaces offers a brilliant case study in adaptive reuse and thoughtful design.About Hauser & WirthHauser & Wirthwas founded in 1992 in Zurich by Iwan Wirth, Manuela Wirth and Ursula Hauser, who were joined in 2000 by Partner and President Marc Payot. Hauser & Wirth represents over 90 artists and estates who have been instrumental in shaping its identity and who are the inspiration for Hauser & Wirths diverse range of activities that engage with art, education, conservation and sustainability.Occupying a former farmstead in Bruton, Hauser & Wirth Somerset hosts a vibrant program of exhibitions, events, learning activities and artist residencies, which connect with the local community and landscape.Surrounding the gallery is a working farm, where alongside herds of cattle and sheep, there is a vineyard, walled garden, beehives and an orchard. The onsite Farm Shop celebrates the best growers, farmers and makers that Somerset has to offer, as well as the produce from the surrounding Durslade Farm