1283	https://www.architecture.com/whats-on/riba-yorkshire-sepn-designing-stories-september-2025	riba	Title: RIBA Yorkshire SEPN: Designing stories: How symbolic gestures differentiate your practice\\nEvent Type: Talks and lectures\\nShort Description: Join Yorkshire's Small and emerging practice network (SEPN) for a for a talk with Paul Iddon and learn how symbolic gestures create emotional connections in architecture.\\nDate: 11 September 2025, 1pm to 2pm\\nPlace: Online\\nContact: riba.yorkshire@riba.orgriba.yorkshire@riba.org\\nCost: Free\\nDescription: Yorkshire's Small and emerging practice network representative Paul Wainwright invites you to join us for the September webinar where we will be joined by Paul Iddon.This session will be on todayscrowded market;small and emerging architectural practices need more than just great designs, they need to create emotional connections that truly resonate with clients.Paul Iddon, architect-turned-marketer and RIBA National Council Member, RIBA North West Member, and Vice President of the Manchester Society of Architects, will provide an insightful online session revealing how a simple, symbolic gesture - a red chair moment - can become the emotional heart of your project. These moments help tell your projects story in a way clients remember and connect with deeply.Drawing on groundbreaking research from behavioural economics and storytelling, Paul explains how clients often make emotional decisions first and then justify them rationally. Understanding this can transform how you communicate your value beyond technical details.Learn practical, actionable techniques to identify and frame these symbolic moments in your work, helping you build trust, stand out in a competitive market, and grow your practice.Plus, get an exclusive preview of Pauls upcoming free CPD course on storytelling and symbolic design tools designed to make your architecture unforgettable.About Paul IddonPaul is an architect and communications expert with over 35 years of experience in practice and brand strategy, specialising in communications with a focus on architect engagement.	RIBA Yorkshire SEPN: Designing stories: How symbolic gestures differentiate your practice	Join RIBA Yorkshire's Small and Emerging Practice Network (SEPN) for an insightful online talk with Paul Iddon on how symbolic gestures create emotional connections in architecture on 11 September 2025.	Join RIBA Yorkshire's Small and Emerging Practice Network (SEPN) for an insightful online talk with Paul Iddon on how symbolic gestures create emotional connections in architecture.	In todays competitive architectural landscape, small and emerging practices need more than just exceptional designs; they require strategies to forge deep emotional connections with clients. This online session, presented by architect and communications expert Paul Iddon, dives into the power of "symbolic gestures"moments that become the emotional core of your architectural projects. Paul will illustrate how seemingly simple actions, like a "red chair" moment, can transform a project's narrative, making it memorable and deeply resonant with clients. Drawing insights from behavioural economics and the art of storytelling, Paul explains that client decisions are often emotionally driven before being rationally justified. Understanding this dynamic is crucial for communicating your practice's unique value beyond technical specifications. Attendees will gain actionable techniques to identify and frame these symbolic moments within their work, enhancing client trust, improving market differentiation, and fostering significant practice growth. This session also offers a sneak peek into Pauls upcoming free CPD course on storytelling and symbolic design tools, ensuring your architecture leaves an unforgettable impression. Attending this webinar will equip architects with innovative communication strategies to elevate their practice and connect more effectively with clients.	11 Se