ving services for a wide range of individuals, including those with learning disabilities, autism, physical disabilities, and complex or challenging behaviours.Stephens work focuses on building strong, long-term partnerships with local authorities, CCGs, and property developers to create sustainable supported living environments. He understands the operational and strategic challenges from the providers side and will be sharing real insight into what care organisations actually need from landlords and investors.Expect an honest, practical look at how to structure property deals that not only work financially but genuinely serve the people theyre meant to support.Guest Speaker 2: Ben GreenBen Green has spent years shaping high-quality, sustainable supported housing schemes across the Midlands and the North of England, creating homes that make a real difference for vulnerable adults.From acquiring the right sites, to working closely with local authorities, the NHS, care providers, and registered providers, Ben has a wealth of experience in navigating the many moving parts needed to deliver tenant-centric schemes.In this session, Ben will share:- How to engage effectively with local authorities- What to look for in providers and partners- Key lessons on structuring successful leases that protect both investors and residents- Insights into meeting the growing demand for supported housingThis is a great opportunity for anyone in the property industry to better understand one of the most impactful and complex areas of housing.Seats are limited, so book early and join a community committed to using property as a force for good.Lets build more than portfolioslets build impact.Book your ticket today.	Property With Purpose Events	This event provides straight-talking insights into Social Housing and Supported Living, bringing together experts to discuss sustainable property strategies and impact-driven investments. Join us on 30 September 2025.	This event provides straight-tal